article.description: — Elijah Weaver came off the bench to tally 16 points to carry Dayton to a 79-41 win over Northern Illinois on Saturday.
article.headline: Weaver scores 16 to lift Dayton past N. Illinois 79-41
article.linkText: Weaver scores 16 to lift Dayton past N. Illinois 79-41
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- — Elijah Weaver came off the bench to tally 16 points to carry Dayton to a 79-41 win over Northern Illinois on Saturday. DaRon Holmes II had 14 points for Dayton (6-3), which won its fifth straight game. Koby Brea added 12 points. Malachi Smith had 11 points. Trendon Hankerson had 7 points for the Huskies (2-6). Anthony Crump also had 7 points. Keshawn Williams had 7 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
